World soccer governing body FIFA
selected Germany-based GoalControl GmbH to be the official goal-
line technology provider for the 2013 Conferederations Cup
tournament in  Brazil .  GoalControl will also provide technology for the 2014 World
Cup in Brazil if its performance meets FIFA requirements at the
Confederations Cup, the governing body said in a statement.  GoalControl was chosen ahead of three other companies, FIFA
said. The Confederations Cup will be played June 15-30.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
